	<text>
		<body>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Abraham Peller</persName> Testimony (doc. 301/1649)</p>
			<p>Original, manuscript, 2 pages 210 x 295 mm, 1 page 210 x 140 mm, Polish language.</p>
			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_01.jpg"/>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Abraham Peller</persName></p>
			<p>Born at <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764274/mszanka.html">Mszanka</placeName> (the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/771804/gorlice.html">Gorlice</placeName> county) in <date when="1894">1894</date></p>
			<p>Residing at <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecz</placeName>, near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName> [recorded by] <persName ref="#ehri_et_bauminger_roza">[Róża]
					Bauminger</persName></p>
			<p>Actions in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecz</placeName></p>
			<p>In the early days of the occupation it was quiet in our town. But on <date when="1942-01-03">January 3, 1942</date>, the excesses
				began. The <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> raided several Jewish homes and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> 8 people who happened to fall into their
				hands. The names of these people are: two <persName ref="#ehri_et_heller">Heller</persName> brothers, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_bornstein">Bornstein</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Łódź</placeName>,
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_gilowa">Gilowa</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html"
				>Łódź</placeName>, a <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">wife</term> of a tailor and
				mother of three <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">children</term>, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_itzinger_chaim">Chaim Itzinger</persName> with his <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">daughter</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_itzinger_regina">Regina</persName>, and <persName ref="#ehri_et_czesniower_izak">Izak Cześniower</persName>.
				It was the so-called <q>town quota</q>. Similar acts of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745"
					type="subject">homicide</term> took place in the nearby towns: in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/771804/gorlice.html"
					>Gorlice</placeName>, and others. Some <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">woman</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName> informed that <persName ref="#ehri_et_zucker">Dr
					Zucker</persName> of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName> had been a commissar during the
				times of the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Soviets</term>. He and his <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">wife</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> on the spot, and their <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">daughters</term> were taken to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecz</placeName>. They were ordered to get out of the car and were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> near my house. My <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">son</term> ran to fetch a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term> because one of the <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">girls</term> was still alive, but her state was hopeless, and she
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> half an hour later. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_fornalik_ignacy">Ignacy Fornalik</persName>, commandant of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term>, informed the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> that some Jews had tried to save a
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">girl</term> who had been sentenced to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term>, and on <date when="1942-02-16">February
					16, 1942</date>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish policemen</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> these <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">boys</term> and their <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">families</term>. My <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">son</term> and I were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term>, too. They blackmailed us to swindle
				us out of money, and they got a pretty large sum. <persName ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielman</persName> was freed immediately, I was
				to be released in the evening, and the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">boys</term>
				at night. But in the meantime the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> arrived, and
				they ordered to have <persName ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielman</persName> and his entire <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">family</term> brought back, and apart from them also <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_schnaps_hinda">Hinda Schnaps</persName> with her two <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">sons</term> and my entire <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">family</term> of seven. All of us were handcuffed in pairs, and at 7
				pm everybody was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term>. I was at the very
				rear, and looked at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term> of my <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">family</term>. Then they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielman</persName>, who was handcuffed with me. He tumbled down, all covered with blood, <pb n="2"
					facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_02.jpg"/> and I fell with him. I was lying in a puddle of blood, and the <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> thought that I was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term>, but they shot me in the arm just to make
				sure. Then they ordered <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish policemen</term> to
				take the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">bodies</term> away. They removed our
				handcuffs, and when they went away for a break, I took advantage of their absence, raised myself and, dripping blood, managed to drag
				myself to the village of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764343/moszczenica.html">Moszczenica</placeName>, 20 kilometres away,
				to a <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term> peasant <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">woman</term>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_jedrzejewska_adela">Adela
					Jędrzejewska</persName>, who was very generous towards me and gave me <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">shelter</term>.</p>
			<p>I learnt from eye-witnesses that on <date when="1942-02-18">February 18</date>, 100 Jews were taken from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecz</placeName>. They were kept in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term> for 4 days, their money was confiscated,
				and after 4 days 69 of them were <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">shot</term> (the
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_schutzer">Schützer</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_gewurz">Gewürz</persName>, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_kleinman">Kleinman</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_wagschaller">Wagschaller</persName>
				<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">families</term>). It turned out that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> was responsible for organising
				this action, and when they got a phone call from the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350"
					>Gestapo</orgName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName>, they had already <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> 31 people. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> blackmailed the Jews and they
				swindled 250 thousand zlotys out of them, saying that if they didn’t pay, another similar action would be carried out. A few months
				later the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> took and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> 14 other Jews. Allegedly, the charge
				against them was was that their brothers were <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1000"
					>communists</term>. The names of some of the victims are: <persName ref="#ehri_et_schneider">Schneider</persName>, a <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">family</term> of five, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kurz"
					>Kurz</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_jakobowicz">Jakóbowicz</persName>, and <persName ref="#ehri_et_wagschal"
					>Wagschal</persName> with his <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">wife</term>.</p>
			<p>In <date when="1942-08">August 1942</date> a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-551" type="subject"
					>liquidation</term> action took place. 170 people were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541"
					type="subject">shot</term> on the spot and buried at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-750"
					type="subject">Jewish cemetery</term>. 700 people were loaded onto <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">cattle cars</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">transported</term> to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-41" type="camp">Bełżec</placeName>. Those who managed to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hide</term> were hunted down by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> and turned over to the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName>. <pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_03.jpg"/> I and
				my <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">brother</term> and two other Jews were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term> at <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_jedrzejewska_adela">Jędrzejewska’s</persName> home, and around 70 other Jews were in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term> in the same village. The commandant of
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> in that village, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_bednarz">Bednarz</persName>, was ordered to conduct a search for the Jews <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term> in the area. He warned us against the
				danger we were in, and we left <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764343/moszczenica.html">Moszczenica</placeName>. On the
				following day, he assembled 70 peasants with pitchforks, and ordered them to look for Jews in the attics. They certainly failed to
				find a single Jew. <persName ref="#ehri_et_bednarz">Bednarz</persName> risked his life several times to save Jews. He was blackmailed,
				and then removed by the commissar of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish
					police</term> from that particular village (of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765673/luzna.html">Łużna</placeName>) to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName>. At present <persName ref="#ehri_et_bednarz"
					>Bednarz</persName> is a <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1006">mayor</term> in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7534761/blazejow.html">Blasdorf</placeName>
				<note type="gloss">Blasdorf bei Schömberg, Polish name: <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7534761/blazejow.html"
						>Błażejów</placeName>.</note> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3096779/kamienna-gora.html">Kamienna
					Góra</placeName>.</p>
			<p>[signed by] <persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Abraham Peller</persName></p>
